article.headline: Temple 45, Penn St. 42
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Ryan Brooks scored 19 points and made a pair of late free throws to lift Temple to a 45-42 win over Penn State on Saturday. Brooks, who was the only Temple player to score in double figures, shot 8-for-18 from the field and grabbed six rebounds for the Owls (6-2). His jumper from the top of the key with 1:32 left to play gave Temple a 43-40 lead. His two free throws with 11.6 seconds to go -- after an offensive foul against the Nittany Lions -- accounted for the final margin. Chris Babb came off the bench to lead Penn State (5-3) with 11 points. The Owls made just 18 of 60 shots (30 percent). The Nittany Lions shot 15-for-43 (34.9 percent).
